- How would you handle multilingual data drift across EN/ES/PT?

## Why This Is Asked

This question tests on-device NLP, low-latency constraints, multilingual support, and privacy-conscious data collection. It also covers labeling workflows, offline evaluation, and phased rollout strategies.

## Key Concepts

- **On-device inference**: Small footprint model (2–5 MB) running directly on the client
- **Multilingual handling**: Language detection with fallback mechanisms for EN/ES/PT
- **Privacy-preserving data**: PII redaction before logging with anonymized feedback collection
- **Evaluation & rollout**: Offline metrics, drift detection, and safe staged deployment with rollback capability

## Code Example

```javascript
function redactPII(text) {
  const patterns = [
    /\b\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}\b/g, // SSN
    /\b\d{16}\b/g,             // Credit card
    /\b[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\.[A-Z|a-z]{2,}\b/g // Email
  ];
  return patterns.reduce((redacted, pattern) => 
    redacted.replace(pattern, '[REDACTED]'), text);
}

async function moderateMessage(message, model) {
  const startTime = performance.now();
  const detectedLang = detectLanguage(message.text);

  if (!supportedLanguages.includes(detectedLang)) {
    return { flagged: false, fallback: true };
  }

  const prediction = await model.classify(message.text);
  const latency = performance.now() - startTime;

  if (latency > 150) {
    console.warn('Latency threshold exceeded:', latency);
  }

  return {
    ...prediction,
    latency,
    lang: detectedLang
  };
}
```

## Why This Is Asked

