## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to combine rule-based extraction with lightweight ML under edge constraints in multilingual contexts.

## Key Concepts
- Hybrid NLP, on-device inference, multilingual/code-switching, latency, privacy, evaluation.

## Code Example
```javascript
function detectFeatures(text){
  const features = ['battery','screen','camera','price'];
  let mentions = features.filter(f => text.toLowerCase().includes(f));
  return mentions;
}
function scoreSentiment(text){
  const pos = ['great','amazing','love','good','excellent'];
  const neg = ['bad','terrible','worst','poor','fail'];
  let s=0; const tokens = text.toLowerCase().split(/\\W+/);
  tokens.forEach(t => { if(pos.includes(t)) s++; if(neg.includes(t)) s--; });
  return s;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you adapt to additional languages and more features?
- How would you handle severe class imbalance or drift over time?

## Why This Is Asked

Assess ability to design end-to-end NLP systems at the edge with privacy, latency, and explainability constraints. This scenario blends multilingual NL understanding, policy translation, and auditable versioning in a cloud-edge ecosystem.

## Key Concepts

- Multilingual intent classification at edge with latency constraints
- Policy translation to concrete firewall/CDN rules with a grammar-based bridge
- Explainability and privacy controls with audit trails in MongoDB

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudocode: mapNLToPolicy NL -> RuleSet
function mapNLToPolicy(nl, locale) {
  const intent = classifyIntent(nl, locale);
  const rules = translateIntentToRules(intent);
  return { intent, rules };
}
```

